==English==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|mistaken}}, from {{bor|en|non|mistaka|t=to take in error, to miscarry}}; equivalent to {{prefix|en|mis|take}}. Cognate with {{cog|is|mistaka|t=to mistake}}, {{cog|sv|missta|t=to mistake}} (before apocope {{m|sv|misstaga}}). Displaced {{cog|enm|misnimen}} and {{cog|enm|misfōn}} from {{cog|ang|misfōn}} (and noun {{l|ang|misfeng}}).

The noun, which replaced earlier {{m|en|mistaking}}, is derived from the verb.

