#* {{circa|1596}} {{w|William Shakespeare}}, ''{{w|King John (play)|King John}}'', Act III, Scene 1,<sup>[http://www.opensourceshakespeare.org/views/plays/play_view.php?WorkID=kingjohn&Act=3&Scene=1&Scope=scene]</sup>
#*: The better act of purposes '''mistook'''
#*: Is to '''mistake''' again; though indirect,
#*: Yet indirection thereby grows direct,
#* '''1716''', {{w|Alexander Pope}} (translator), ''The {{w|Iliad}} of {{w|Homer}}'', London: Bernard Lintott, Volume 2, Book 8, lines 151-152, p. 252,<sup>[http://name.umdl.umich.edu/004836009.0001.002]</sup>
